com.esri.mo2.map.draw
Interface ScaleDependentRenderer

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, LegendInfo, Renderer
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseScaleDependentRenderer
public interface ScaleDependentRenderer
extends Renderer

A ScaleDependentRenderer is a wrapper for another Renderer. It delegates rendering the wrapped Renderer, only when the current Display scale is within a certain scale range. Thus, when the Map is zoomed in enough that its scale is between the maximumScale and minimumScale, the wrapped renderer will draw. When the map zooms in enough that its current scale is smaller than the minimumScale, the wrapped renderer will not draw.

If you want to have multiple scale ranges, then you can group a number of ScaleDependentRenderers using the GroupRenderer.

The scale that is referred to here, is a "contrived" scale equal to the number of world coordinate units per pixels. You can obtain the current scale value from the Map at any time by getting the map's Scale property.

For an example of this interface in use, see the sample code that goes with the symbology chapter in the book: MapObjects -- Java Developer's Guide

public boolean inRange(double scale)
Determine if the given scale value is within the range defined within this ScaleDependentRenderer. This is just equivalent to determining if MinScale <= scale <= MaxScale

Returns:
true == in range, false == otherwise

inRange
